    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-15T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-15T10:00:00-05:00" n="552"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/201: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-15T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 15, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>208. Provisional President <persName corresp="#p_BEGB1">Blanche</persName> named
                    Cabinet last night headed by <persName corresp="#p_BJE1">Ernesto Barros
                        Jarpa</persName> as Minister of the Interior. <persName corresp="#p_BEL1"
                        >Barriga</persName> continues as Minister of Foreign Affairs. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MF1">Francisco Mardones</persName> is Minister of Finance;
                        <persName corresp="#p_RJA1">Juan Antonio Rios</persName>, Minister of
                    Justice; <persName corresp="#p_OGL1">General Otero</persName>, Minister of War;
                    Admiral <persName corresp="#p_MJM3">Montalva</persName>, Minister of Marine;
                        <persName corresp="#p_LG1">Gustavo Lira</persName>, Minister of Fomento; and
                        <persName corresp="#p_EF1">Fidel Estay</persName>, Minister of Labor.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MBA1">Merino</persName> and his supporters surrendered
                    this morning at Ovalle.</p>
                <p>No American interests suffered in this political turnover. Santiago is quiet.</p>
                <p>Government has promised Presidential as well as Congressional elections October
                    30th, maintenance of order and limitation of administration of country to a
                    minimum required for normal conditions until regularly elected Government
                    assumes power.</p>
                <p>Constitutional forms were followed in turning over power to <persName
                        corresp="#p_BEGB1">Blanche</persName> and therefore countries which
                    recognized <persName corresp="#p_DCG1">Dávila</persName> will continue relations
                    with the new regime.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
